  <body id="msgFeedSummaryBody" selected="false">
    <img src="http://www.mediacurrent.com/sites/default/files/imagecache/thumb_blog_spotlight/contentprivacy.png" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-thumb_blog_spotlight imagecache-default imagecache-thumb_blog_spotlight_default" width="200" height="150" /> <p>On Drupal 6 it was difficult to add fields to user profiles – sites were limited to using a minimal set of field types using the built-in Profile module and couldn’t use the normal <a href="http://drupal.org/project/cck">CCK</a> fields. The workaround most commonly used to get beyond this was to use the <a href="https://drupal.org/project/content_profile" target="_blank">Content Profile module</a> which allowed use of an actual content type to house the user profile fields that were needed.</p>
